Written script for Login Azure, listing VM, Starting VM, login VM via SSH


Azure Application Gateway : is a web traffic load balancer that enables you to manage and route traffic to your web applications. 
Web Application Firewall (WAF) : provides protection against web vulnerabilities. 
  Key features include:
    - Load Balancing: Distributes incoming traffic across multiple servers to ensure no single server is overwhelmed.
    - SSL Termination: Offloads SSL processing, improving the efficiency of web servers.
    - Web Application Firewall (WAF): Protects web applications from common web vulnerabilities and exploits.

Azure Load Balancer : distributes incoming network traffic across multiple servers to ensure no single server is overwhelmed.
  - Load Balancing Algorithms, Availability Sets, Inbound and Outbound Traffic
Azure DNS : is a scalable and secure domain hosting service. It provides name resolution using the Microsoft Azure infrastructure.
  - Domain Hosting, Integration with Azure Services, Global Availability
Azure Firewall : is a managed, cloud-based network security service that protects your Azure Virtual Network resources.
  - Stateful Firewall, Application FQDN Filtering, Threat Intelligence Integration
Virtual Network Peering : allows connecting Azure Virtual Networks directly, enabling resources in one VNet to communicate with resources in another.
  - Global VNet Peering, Transitive Routing
VNet Gateway enables secure communication between on-premises networks and Azure Virtual Networks.
  - Site-to-Site VPN, Point-to-Site VPN
Azure VPN Gateway : provides secure, site-to-site connectivity between your on-premises network and Azure.
  - IPsec/IKE VPN Protocols, High Availability, BGP Support.
